<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Bahá’í Text Annotation Tool</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/chrome-extension.css">
    <link rel="icon" href="images/dbs-favicon.png" type="image/png">
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('partials/header', { mini: false }) %>
    <main>
        <section class="content-area">
            <div class="extension-hero">
                <h1>Deepen Your Study</h1>
                <p class="hero-text">An interactive sidebar for the Baha'i reference libraries, designed to help you organize concepts and surface hidden gems for the research community.</p>
                <a href="#" class="cta-button">Add to Chrome</a>
            </div>

            <hr class="divider">

            <div class="feature-grid">
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h2>Personal Study & Tagging</h2>
                    <p>Transform how you interact with the Writings. Highlight passages and assign custom "tags" to track specific themes or subjects. Arrange your tags into a personal hierarchy, creating a structured map of your own learning and discovery. All items created here remain private and exclusive to you.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h2>Uncover Hidden Gems</h2>
                    <p>Help the community by identifying unique items scattered across digital archives. By labeling Tablets in <em>Star of the West</em> or specific letters in <em>Bahá’í News</em>, you help researchers instantly locate high-value documents that were previously difficult to find.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h2>Powering the Future</h2>
                    <p>Your categorized study notes do more than organize your own thoughts—they improve the collective intelligence of the community. This data directly enhances the hybrid RAG AI at <a href="https://bahai.chat">Bahai.chat</a>, helping it provide more accurate and context-aware answers.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <hr class="divider" style="margin-top: 50px;">

            <h2 style="text-align: center; color: #005bb5;">Look Inside the Extension</h2>
            
            <div class="carousel-container">
                <div class="carousel-slide fade">
                    <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bahaipedia/digitalbahairesources/refs/heads/main/public/images/chrome-extension-tags.png" alt="Screenshot of Tagging Tab">
                    <div class="slide-caption">
                        <h3>Tab 1: The Tagging Interface</h3>
                        <p>This tab allows you to highlight text on bahai.org/library or bahai.works, and assign an existing tag or create a new one. You can see your existing tags for quick access.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            
                <div class="carousel-slide fade">
                    <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bahaipedia/digitalbahairesources/refs/heads/main/public/images/chrome-extension-label.png" alt="Screenshot of Hierarchy Tab">
                    <div class="slide-caption">
                        <h3>Tab 2: Hierarchy Manager</h3>
                        <p>Use this tab when viewing large periodicals like Star of the West. Define the boundaries of specific items (e.g., a Tablet, a letter) and categorize its type to help researchers find it later.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            
                <div class="carousel-slide fade">
                    <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bahaipedia/digitalbahairesources/refs/heads/main/public/images/chrome-extension-qanda.png" alt="Screenshot of Item Identifier Tab">
                    <div class="slide-caption">
                        <h3>Tab 3: Crowdsourced Item Identifier</h3>
                        <p>[Placeholder explanation: Use this tab when viewing large periodicals like Star of the West. Define the boundaries of specific items (e.g., a Tablet, a letter) and categorize its type to help researchers find it later.]</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                 <div class="carousel-slide fade">
                    <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bahaipedia/digitalbahairesources/refs/heads/main/public/images/chrome-extension-link.png" alt="Screenshot of Settings Tab">
                    <div class="slide-caption">
                        <h3>Tab 4: Settings & Export</h3>
                        <p>[Placeholder explanation: Manage your account connection, export your personal tag data, and adjust extension preferences here.]</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            
                <a class="prev" onclick="plusSlides(-1)">&#10094;</a>
                <a class="next" onclick="plusSlides(1)">&#10095;</a>
            </div>

        </section>
    </main>
    <%- include('partials/footer') %>

    <script>
        let slideIndex = 1;
        showSlides(slideIndex);

        // Next/previous controls
        function plusSlides(n) {
        showSlides(slideIndex += n);
        }

        // Thumbnail image controls
        function currentSlide(n) {
        showSlides(slideIndex = n);
        }

        function showSlides(n) {
        let i;
        let slides = document.getElementsByClassName("carousel-slide");
        if (n > slides.length) {slideIndex = 1}
        if (n < 1) {slideIndex = slides.length}
        for (i = 0; i < slides.length; i++) {
            slides[i].style.display = "none";
        }
        slides[slideIndex-1].style.display = "block";
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
